    "side_effects_description": "The possible side effects of using Thamnochortus nutans improperly include experiencing nausea, dizziness, and skin irritation. This is due to the plant's toxic compounds, specifically sesquiterpene lactones and sesquiterpenoids, which can cause gastrointestinal and neurological symptoms. Ingesting or applying the plant improperly can lead to the absorption of these toxic compounds, resulting in nausea, dizziness, and skin irritation. The severity of these side effects can vary depending on the method of use, dosage, and individual tolerance. Proper identification, handling, and use of Thamnochortus nutans are essential to minimize the risk of adverse reactions.",
